thread.title: Clinton opposes TPP deal
thread.title_full: Clinton opposes TPP deal | Business Spectator

author: AP
title: Clinton opposes TPP deal
text:
US Democratic presidential candidate Hillary Clinton says she opposes the big Pacific Rim trade accord backed by President Barack Obama.
She said in an interview with the broadcaster PBS on Wednesday there were too many "unanswered questions" about the Trans-Pacific Partnership.
"What I know about it as of today, I am not in favour."
The free trade deal, which includes Australia, backed by the administration has been opposed by liberal Democrats and labour unions.
Ms Clinton helped lay the foundation for the deal as Mr Obama's secretary of state.
She joins Democratic rivals Bernie Sanders and Martin O'Malley, who warn it could lead to lost American jobs.
The pact is central to Mr Obama's attempt to engage with Asia to offset a rising Chinese influence in the region.
